rail is a short 13.5 minute documentary film made by geoffrey jones for british transport films between 1963 and 1967 , prompted by the success of snow .   the " pure cinema " film illustrated the transition from steam powered locomotives to diesel and electric traction which was taking place during that period .   nominated for a bafta film award for best short film in 1968 , it took four years to make , during which time british railways changed their livery which required jones to modify his plans for the film on his return from filming trinidad and tobago in 1964 .